<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Filmmaker <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Waters </PERSON> says there are similarities between his first PG-rated movie and his 1972 midnight classic `` Pink Flamingos,'' which is still outraging audiences. `` Hairspray,'' a comedy about an overweight girl who becomes a star on a local television dance show, makes its debut this week. Divine, the 300-pound transvestite star of `` Pink Flamingos'' plays the mother of the heroine of `` Hairspray.'' `` I knew this was one of the few obsessions I ever had that would be palatable to -LRB- general -RRB- movie executives,'' the 41-year-old Waters said of `` Hairspray'' in an interview published Sunday in <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>. `` The sensibility and sense of humor in ` Hairspray' is the same of ` Pink Flamingos.' The difference is that I do n't have the rage at 41. I'd be a jerk.''
