<HEAD>Man Fatally Shot With Crossbow</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man awakened by three intruders searching his apartment for a stolen jacket fatally shot one of them with a crossbow, authorities said. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hucek </PERSON>, 21, was killed after he and his two companions burst into <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON>'s apartment early Saturday, according to <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Orange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriff </ORGANIZATION>'s office. <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Farmer </PERSON> and <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Roehrick </PERSON> were being held without bail after being charged with burglary and second-degree murder under a state law that permits such prosecution for those involved in a felony resulting in death. `` It was pretty traumatic,'' said the 27-year-old <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON>, who was shot in the leg. <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said <PERSON> Hucek </PERSON>, <PERSON> Roehrick </PERSON>, 22, and <PERSON> Farmer </PERSON>, 25, spotted <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON>'s roommate when they were out driving late Friday. The three thought that the roommate, <PERSON> Kurt </PERSON> <PERSON> Chaillet </PERSON>, had something to do with the theft of an expensive leather jacket that belonged to one of them, <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said. Chaillet, 25, joined the three for driving and beer drinking and later took them back to the apartment, where they confronted him with their suspicions and demanded to search the apartment, <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said. The search, which turned up no leather jacket, quickly turned into a ransacking, and the noise woke <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON>, <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said. `` He told them to get out,'' <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said. When they refused, <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON> armed himself with a screwdriver and forced them out. He locked and bolted the door, but the three kicked in the door and pushed their way inside, where <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON> had armed himself with a crossbow. He fired once, striking <PERSON> Hucek </PERSON> in the chest and killing him. The violence continued as Chaillet ran to call authorities. The fight between Farmer, <PERSON> Roehrick </PERSON> and <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON> moved into the parking lot, where <PERSON> Roehrick </PERSON> pulled a gun from his truck and shot twice, hitting <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON> in the leg, <PERSON> Solomons </PERSON> said. When deputies arrived, they found Farmer and <PERSON> Roehrick </PERSON> in the parking lot and <PERSON> Hedgecock </PERSON> sitting on his couch.
