ered further hearings to determine the amount. In the appeal acted on today, <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION> officials said <PERSON> Tarkanian </PERSON> was treated fairly. They also argued that <PERSON> Tarkanian </PERSON> got a `` home court'' advantage by taking his case to a <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> state judge who overruled the findings of the <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION> investigators. The judge ruled `` in favor of a popular, local personality'' substituting his views `` for that of 21 independent teachers and administrators who heard all of the evidence,'' the <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION>'s appeal said. The case is <ORGANIZATION> NCAA </ORGANIZATION> vs. <PERSON> Tarkanian </PERSON>, 87-1061.
