<BYLINE>By MARTIN STEINBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 A forest fire sparked by a hiker's campfire and fanned by 90 mph gusts slowed today after threatening up to 100 houses near <LOCATION> Boulder </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Colo. </LOCATION>, and a wind-whipped 2,400-acre blaze in <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION> destroyed at least four houses. No injuries were reported. Roads in <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION>'s Sunshine Canyon area were closed late Sunday and occupants of one apartment building near the blaze voluntarily left the building, as did residents of five homes. But no evacuations were ordered and the roads were reopened today. The fire grew to more than 200 acres of grass and light timber by early today, the <ORGANIZATION> Boulder </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sheriff </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said. The area was under a high wind warning with 90 mph gusts reported. Wind had been expected to reach 100 mph today, but at 3 a.m. it subsided to gusts of no more than 30 mph and there was an early morning calm of 6 mph, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Weather </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> said. `` The fire has laid down considerably since last night,'' said firefighter <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Gregg </PERSON>. `` It's not contained in the sense that there is no fire line around the fire completely, but it's not spreading out of control as it was last night when the winds were high.'' Strong wind blew through much of the <ORGANIZATION> Rockies </ORGANIZATION> on Sunday. Afternoon and evening wind gusted to 65 mph in <LOCATION> Cody </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Wyo. </LOCATION>, and near <LOCATION> Calgary </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Alberta </LOCATION>, chinook wind forced postponement of the final heats of the men's two-man bobsled competition at the Winter Olympics. The Colorado fire started on <LOCATION> Boulder </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Mountain </LOCATION> <LOCAT