No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fire raced through a ski resort hotel in <LOCATION> Bulgaria </LOCATION> before dawn today, killing six people and injuring 36 others, <LOCATION> Bulgaria </LOCATION>'s official news agency reported. The news agency <ORGANIZATION> BTA </ORGANIZATION> said the fire in <LOCATION> Borovets </LOCATION>, a ski resort 22 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Sofia </LOCATION>, began at 3 a.m. `` Measures were taken to put out the blaze but the building was quickly engulfed in flames,'' said the <ORGANIZATION> BTA </ORGANIZATION> report received in <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION>. `` In the panic that followed, six people died.'' The agency said two of the dead were Dutch, one was Bulgarian and three had not been identified. Of the 36 injured, <ORGANIZATION> BTA </ORGANIZATION> said 17 were British, four Soviet, five West German, seven Greek, two Danish and one Dutch, according to <ORGANIZATION> BTA </ORGANIZATION>. Their names were not released. `` The causes of the fire are still not known,'' the news agency said, adding a commission was appointed to investigate `` the tragic accident.'' <ORGANIZATION> BTA </ORGANIZATION> identified the dead Dutch visitors as `` Ms. Ever <PERSON> Vanderberg </PERSON>'' and `` Mr. <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Zekelenburg </PERSON>.'' Their home towns were not made public. The name of the dead Bulgarian was not reported. An unidentified man who answered the telephone at the Bulgarian state tourist office in <PERSON> Borovets </PERSON> said the 170-bed hotel was destroyed in the blaze. He refused to give further details about the fire. Initial reports from Western diplomats in <LOCATION> Sofia </LOCATION> said Britons, West Germans and Dutch tourists were injured when they jumped out hotel windows to escape the blaze at the <LOCATION> Moussala </LOCATION> hotel. The diplomats, contacted by telephone from <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION>, spoke on condition of anonymity. Several Western embassies said they had sent diplomats to <PERSON> Borovets </