decisive, ineffective, inefficient regulation of the commercial nuclear industry.'' <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Ingram </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> NRC </ORGANIZATION>, said the agency had no immediate comment on the details of the legislation but added that `` a majority of the commission supports a single administrator concept.'' The bill was approved by voice vote of the <ORGANIZATION> Environment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Works </ORGANIZATION> subcommittee on nuclear regulation.
