<BYLINE>By NORMAN BLACK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Military Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Webb </PERSON> resigned today, saying he is `` unable to support'' <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON>'s decision to abandon the goal of a 600-ship fleet and criticizing <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON>'s leadership in the Pentagon. `` This building needs to be led,'' <PERSON> Webb </PERSON> told reporters. `` It needs leadership. It needs some vision. I'm saying that if I had a piece of advice to give to Secretary <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON>, it would be to spend a lot more time with the top leaders in this building. `` He's been spending a lot of time with the <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> and a lot of time on the Hill. I think they -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> leaders -RRB- need to feel his vision and to understand what he believes in.'' <PERSON> Webb </PERSON>, 42, has held the job less than a year. A highly-decorated Marine veteran of <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> combat, he was the author of `` Fields of Fire,'' a best-selling novel about the war in <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>. In his letter of resignation to President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>, <PERSON> Webb </PERSON> said he decided to leave because he could not support the fiscal 1989 <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> budget proposal crafted by <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON>. Presidential spokesman <PERSON> Marlin </PERSON> <PERSON> Fitzwater </PERSON> said, `` Secretary <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON> is having to make some very difficult adjustments in the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> to accommodate budgetary reductions. Secretary <PERSON> Webb </PERSON> indicates he is unable to operate under these constraints, but I know the president feels he has given very valuable service to the country, and will work with Secretary <PERSON> Carlucci </PERSON> to find a replace