from public witnesses. Dr. <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Teller </PERSON>, the physicist who is considered the father of both the hydrogen bomb and <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>'s Star Wars program, told the foreign relations panel he thought the fights over the meanings of treaties were `` senseless debates.'' <PERSON> Teller </PERSON> said he supports the treaty, although he is deeply distrustful of the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. Speaking of the treaty, he said, `` my personal approach is careful, doubtful, yet positive,'' he said.
