<HEAD>Trafficker Who Told Of Payoffs To Noriega To Be Sentenced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A principal witness in the drug conspiracy case against Panamanian Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> faces up to 20 years in prison when sentenced this week for his part in the ring which smuggled 500,000 pounds of marijuana and 1 -LCB- tons of cocaine into the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. But <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON>, 35, expects leniency for his testimony against <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, which included <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON>'s report that he made made $ 900,000 in payoffs to the Panamanian strongman. `` Obviously, he's hoping he wo n't have to spend too much time in jail,'' said <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> DeGuerin </PERSON>, <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON>'s friend and defense attorney in <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON> pleaded guilty a year ago during the trial of his partner, <PERSON> Leigh </PERSON> <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Ritch </PERSON>, and has since emerged as a principal witness against <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> in the <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> conspiracy case. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> also faces separate racketeering and drug charges in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Ritch </PERSON>, 34, is serving a sentence of 30 years in prison. In the <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> case, <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON> testified he gave <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON> cash and jewelry in exchange for Panamanian banking services and military protection. <PERSON> Kalish </PERSON> told a <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> panel last month that he became attracted to <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> in 1983 because of its international banking facilities. He flew there with $ 2.4 million in cash and met with <PERSON> Cesar </PERSON> <PERSON> Rodriguez </PERSON> <PERSON> Contreras </PERSON> at the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZ