 These are some of the top names in <ORGANIZATION> NATO </ORGANIZATION>: <PERSON> PIERRE </PERSON> <PERSON> HARMEL </PERSON> _ A Belgian law professor, premier and <ORGANIZATION> Cabinet </ORGANIZATION> minister, his 1967 report on the alliance's long-term goals remains the basis of <ORGANIZATION> NATO </ORGANIZATION> strategy. It was the Harmel Report that identified the twin themes of seeking to establish an East-West detente while maintaining strong defenses.
