 The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION>, as part of the `` Taxes and Your Money'' Special Edition, misstated the formula for determining what portion of Social Security benefits is taxable. The starting point for the calculation is total income subject to tax plus half the Social Security benefits.
