 Removing old wallpaper before a refinishing project can be done quicker and easier with a variable temperature control heat gun. Here are some tips from <PERSON> Harry </PERSON> <PERSON> W. </PERSON> <PERSON> Earl </PERSON>, brand manager for <ORGANIZATION> Emhart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s Thermostrip: _ Moisten a section of the old wallpaper with water. _ Set the heat gun at full power, holding the nozzle three inches from the wall and direct the hot air at a seam. _ As adhesive begins to soften, gently loosen the paper with a scraper, then peel off. _ Continue moistening the wallpaper throughout the process.
