<HEAD>Drexel Acknowledges SEC Staff Recommended Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 For the first time, <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> has acknowledged publicly that the staff of the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> has recommended that <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> and some of its employees face civil charges. The investment firm also confirmed it has been under investigation by a federal grand jury. The information is contained in a preliminary prospectus for <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Income </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fund </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a new high-yield `` junk bond'' fund being <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> is underwriting. Such information routinely is required in prospectuses to warn would-be investors of potential risk. The document describing the fund was dated Feb. 16 and mailed to investors last week. It stated <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> had advised the fund about the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> staff recomendations for civil actions against the firm and against some employees `` relating to transactions, some of which may have involved ` high yield' bonds.'' `` No assurance can be given that the results of any such <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> action or grand jury investigation will not have an adverse effect on <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and-or the market for ` high yield' bonds, a market in which <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> is an important participant,'' the prospectus said Despite the caveat, sales of the fund apparently were unaffected on Friday, its first trading day, when it closed unchanged at $ 10 per share. <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Anreder </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>'s chief spokesman, on Monday declined to comment outside of the information contained in the prospectus. In January, <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> and several ranking employees _ including junk-bond chief <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Milken </PERSON> _ reportedly were informed that the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> staff had decided to recommend charges of violations of security laws. On Jan. 27, the <ORGANIZATION> Wall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Street </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Journal </ORGANIZATION> said the focus of the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>'s investigation of <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> involved possible violations of securities laws in corporate takeover situations, particularly `` stock parking'' _ the hiding of true ownership of stock in someone else's The practice can be used to evade <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> reporting requirements. <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> and the employees have lodged their opposition to the decision with the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION>, but the federal agency had not decided whether to proceed, according to the prospectus. The firm previously has acknowledged that an investigation was under way, but it has maintained that no wrongdoing took place. The prospectus says <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> has furnished documents to a federal grand jury in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, and some employees have appeared before the panel. <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> reportedly has been the object of government scrutiny since the breaking of the scandal surrounding former arbitrager <PERSON> Ivan </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Boesky </PERSON>, because of the firm's extensive involvement in financing of corporate takeovers involved in the scandal.
