<HEAD>Dollar Falls Marginally, Stock Prices Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar fell marginally against the Japanese yen in early trading Tuesday, while stock prices posted a moderate advance. The dollar opened at 129.27 yen, down 0.68 yen from Monday's close of 129.95 yen on the <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> foreign exchange market Currency dealers said there were no specific incentives affecting the exchange dealings, but that the dollar remained under pressure because of Japanese concerns about the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> economy. On the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Nikkei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Average </ORGANIZATION> of 225 selected issues, which rose 73.30 points Monday, gained another 25.71 points or 0.1 percent in early trading, moving to 24,872.42.
